From Patrick C Leger Subject Re thoughts on christians Excerpts from Apr Re thoughts on christians by Dave F I'm sick of religious types being pampered looked out for and WORST OF ALL respected more than There must be an end in I think it'd help if we got a couple good atheists or even some good steadfast agnostics in some high political When was the last time we had an openly atheist president Have we ever I don't actually know these aren't rhetorical How 'bout some Supreme court justices One thing that really ticked me off a while ago was an ad for a news program on a local promo said something like Who are these cults and why do they prey on the young EVER HEAR OF BAPTISM AT BIRTH If that isn't preying on the young I don't know what I used to be ack barf a Catholic and was even thereafter I decided it was a load of My mom who really insisted that I continue to go to church felt it was her duty to bring me up as a believer That was one of the more presumptuous things I've heard in my I suggested we go talk to the priest and she The priest was amazingly cool about basically said that if I didn't believe it there was no good in forcing it on Actually I guess he wasn't amazingly cool about it His response is what you'd hope for indeed expect from a human I s'pose I just didn't expect I find it absurd that religion exists Yet I can also see its usefulness to Facing up to the fact that you're just going to be worm food in a few decades and that there isn't some cosmic purpose to humanity and the universe can be pretty difficult for some Having a readily available pre digested solution to this is pretty attractive if you're either a gullible enough b willing to suspend your reasoning abilities for the piece of mind or c have had the stuff rammed down your throat for as long as you can Religion in general provides a nice patch for some human weaknesses Organized religion provides a nice way to keep a population under Chris Chris Leger Sophomore Carnegie Mellon Computer Engineering you don't like what somebody is saying you can always ignore them